text: Ivanchug () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Ivanchugsky Selsoviet, Kamyzyaksky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 1,423 as of 2010. There are 14 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Gandurino River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kamyzyaksky District
title: Ivanchug
